A redox-regulated disulphide may form between Fibrinogen beta chain and Fibrinogen gamma chain at these cysteines. However, the redox score of this cysteine pair is lower than any known redox-active disulphide.

A redox-regulated disulphide may form between Fibrinogen beta chain and Fibrinogen gamma chain at these cysteines. However, the redox score of this cysteine pair is lower than any known redox-active disulphide.

A redox-regulated disulphide may form between Fibrinogen beta chain and Fibrinogen gamma chain at these cysteines. However, the redox score of this cysteine pair is lower than any known redox-active disulphide.
